    },
    {
      "account": "American Express ****7993",
      "letter_text": "Dear American Express,\n\nI am disputing the inaccurate reporting of my account (ending in 7993) under the Fair Credit Reporting Act, 15 U.S.C. § 1681i(a)(1)(A). Your reporting shows a status of 'late_30' while simultaneously indicating a 90-day late payment in the late_payments field. This inconsistency constitutes inaccurate reporting.\n\nBecause the reported delinquency status does not match the actual payment history, therefore the information is false and misleading under FCRA. I demand correction to accurately reflect the account status or deletion if the discrepancy cannot be resolved.\n\nPlease investigate and provide written confirmation of the correction within 15 days as required by 15 U.S.C. § 1681i(a)(6).\n\nSincerely,\nXXXX XXXX",
      "statute_citations": ["15 U.S.C. § 1681i(a)(1)(A)", "15 U.S.C. § 1681i(a)(6)"]
    },
