      "account": "Aidvantage ****9337",
      "letter_text": "Dear Aidvantage,\n\nI am disputing the inaccurate reporting of my account (ending in 9337) under the Fair Credit Reporting Act, 15 U.S.C. § 1681i(a)(1)(A). The account shows a bankruptcy status with an outstanding balance of $16,789. If this debt was discharged in bankruptcy, federal law requires that the balance be reported as $0.\n\nBecause reporting a balance on a discharged bankruptcy debt is inaccurate, therefore this violates FCRA's requirement for accurate reporting. I demand correction of the balance to $0 or deletion of the tradeline if the debt was indeed discharged.\n\nPlease provide written confirmation of the correction within 15 days as required by 15 U.S.C. § 1681i(a)(6).\n\nSincerely,\nXXXX XXXX",
